The doyen of sports journalism and Founder and Executive Chairman of Complete Communications Limited, publishers of Complete Sports and Success Digest, Pastor (Dr.) Emmanuel Sunny Ojeagbase will be buried in the United States of America on Friday, April 1. SO as he was fondly called, passed on to glory on 26 February in Atlanta, USA, after a brief illness. He was 71 years old. In a statement signed on behalf of the family by the deceased son, Julius Ojeagbase, ‘there would be a Service of Songs for Pastor (Dr.) Emmanuel Sunny Ojeagbase on Thursday, March 31 at Hillcrest Events Centre, No. 4, Ago Palace Way Okota, Lagos at 4.00 pm, local time.   Lagos SWAN condoles with Lanipekun’s family     Osimhen dismisses links with EPL teams     Aruna drops to 14th in ITTF ranking   Though attendance is strictly by invitation and will be restricted to family members, friends, business associates, and staff of Pst. (Dr.) Ojeagbase, the general public at home and abroad will, however, be able to link up to the service by virtual means via the  Zoom Meeting ID: 835 3369 3272 with Passcode: 356974. Meanwhile, the Service of Songs will be conducted by ministers from the Living Faith Church, Cannanland, Ota while The burial ceremony venue is Eternal Hills Funeral Home, 3594 Stone Mountain Hwy, Snellville, Atlanta, Georgia. Time is 11.00 am in Atlanta (4.00 pm in Nigeria).